tedepublish <= :currenttime')\r\n            ->andWhere('datedepublish > :zeroday')\r\n            ->andWhere('datechanged < datedepublish')\r\n            ->setParameter('status', 'published')\r\n            ->setParameter('zeroday', '1900-01-01 00:00:01')\r\n        ;\r\n```\r\n\r\nSince the second part again starts with `where()`, resetting the where conditions and thus removing the status condition.\r\n\r\n**Solution**\r\nChange `TimedRecord->getHoldQuery()` to start with `andWhere` onstead of `where`.\r\n\r\n\r\n**Note**\r\nThis error can also be found in `getTimedPublishQuery`. It doesnt hurt there, as the status condition is readded there.\r\n\r\nDetails\r\n-------\r\n\r\n - Relevant Bolt Version: 3.2, 3.3, 3.4\r\n - Install type: Composer install\r\n - PHP version: 5.6\r\n - Used web server: Apache\r\n\r\nReproduction\r\n------------\r\nAdd a logger command to the `TimedRecordgetTimedRecords()` to line 215 before executing the query and check the generated query (and the results) in your logs.\r\n\r\n```\r\n$this->systemLogger->warning(\"QUERY::\".$query->getSQL(), []);\r\n$this->systemLogger->warning(\"PARAMETERS::\".print_r($query->getParameters(),true), []);\r\n```\r\n","score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/bolt/bolt/issues/7322","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/bolt/bolt","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/bolt/bolt/issues/7322/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/bolt/bolt/issues/7322/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/bolt/bolt/issues/7322/events","html_url":"https://github.com/bolt/bolt/issues/7322","id":293657302,"number":7322,"title":"Translation of ContentTypes #2","user":{"login":"develth","id":3374563,"avatar_url":"https://avatars0.githubusercontent.com/u/3374563?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/develth","html_url":"https://github.com/develth","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/develth/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/u